definitions.definition: ( transitive ) To bore through an existing hole, generally to correct its shape, or to enlarge .
examples: If you want to keep using that rifle, you'll have to rebore the barrel.
The cylinders of your engine are so worn the rings don't seal any more; you have to have it rebored to stop it from burning oil.

main_definition: ( transitive ) To bore through an existing hole, generally to correct its shape, or to enlarge .

definitions.definition: simple past and past participle of rebear , generally used in the context of Christianity.
examples: And on that day the Lord rebore me and I was reborn.

main_definition: ( transitive , rare ) simple past and past participle of rebear , generally used in the context of Christianity.
